'''DCAP-BTLS''' is an [[mnemonic]] [[acronym]] to remember specific soft tissue injuries to look for during a person's [[Health assessment|assessment]] after a [[trauma (medicine)|traumatic]] injury.<ref name="EMT">{{cite book |author=Ed Dickinson; Dan Limmer; O'Keefe, Michael F.; Grant, Harvey D.; Bob Murray |title=Emergency Care (11th Edition) |publisher=Prentice Hall |location=Englewood Cliffs, N.J |year=2008 |pages=251–3 |isbn=0-13-500524-8}}</ref><ref name="tabers">{{cite book |author1=Taber, Clarence Wilbur |author2=Venes, Donald |title=Taber's cyclopedic medical dictionary |publisher=F A Davis Co |location= |year=2009 |page=579 |isbn=0-8036-1559-0}}</ref> This is a key component during a [[rapid trauma assessment]].
==Meaning== The parts of the mnemonic are:<ref name=tabers/> * [[Deformity|Deformities]] * [[Bruise|Contusions]] * [[Abrasion (medical) | Abrasion]] * [[Penetrating trauma|Penetrations]] * [[Burn]] * [[Tenderness (medicine)|Tenderness]] * [[Wound#Laceration|Lacerations]] * [[Swelling (medical)|Swelling]]
