{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}} :''For others similarly named, see the [[James Aitchison (disambiguation)|James Aitchison]] navigation page'' {{Infobox person | birth_date = 28 October 1835 | birth_place = [[Neemuch]], India |death_date=30 September 1898 |death_place=[[Kew Green]], London |occupation=surgeon and botanist }} '''James Edward Tierney Aitchison''' MD LLD CIE {{Post-nominals|post-noms=[[Fellow of the Royal Society of Edinburgh|FRSE]] [[Fellow of the Royal Society of London|FRS]] [[FRCSE]]}} (28 October 1835 – 30 September 1898)<ref name="Waterston">{{cite book |last1=Waterston |first1=Charles D |last2=Macmillan Shearer |first2=A |title=Former Fellows of the Royal Society of Edinburgh 1783-2002: Biographical Index |url=http://www.rse.org.uk/cms/files/fellows/biographical_index/fells_indexp1.pdf |accessdate=25 November 2011 |volume=I |date=July 2006 |publisher=[[The Royal Society of Edinburgh]] |location=Edinburgh |isbn=978-0-902198-84-5}}</ref> was a Scottish surgeon and botanist.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=t7wUAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA224 ''Transactions and proceedings of the Botanical Society of Edinburgh''], Volume 21, Botanical Society of Edinburgh, 1900</ref>
==Life==
He was the son of Major James Aitchison, HEICS, and was educated at [[Lasswade High School Centre|Lasswade Parish School]], [[Dalkeith High School|Dalkeith Grammar School]] and the [[Edinburgh Academy]].<ref> http://www.royalsoced.org.uk/cms/files/fellows/biographical_index/fells_indexp1.pdf</ref><ref>{{Who's Who | surname = AITCHISON | othernames = James Edward Tierney | id = U183089 | type = was | volume = 2018 | edition = online}} {{subscription required}}</ref> He obtained his doctorate in medicine at the [[University of Edinburgh]] in 1858, and then entered the Bengal Medical Service. He harvested plants in [[India]] from 1861 to 1872, in [[Afghanistan]] from 1879 to 1885 and occasionally in [[Ireland]] 1867 to 1869. He published a catalogue of plants of Punjab and Sindh in 1869, "On the flora of Kuram Valley, etc.. Afghanistan" in the ''Journal of the [[Linnean Society]]'' in 1880&ndash;1881 and various other publications in the publications of the Linnean Society of London (he was a member from 1863). He became a member of the [[Royal Society]] in 1883.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=L22YAN19XOIC&pg=PA614 ''Nature: international journal of science''], Volume 27, Sir Norman Lockyer, Macmillan Journals ltd., 1883</ref> His [[herbarium]] is preserved in the [[Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew]], and [[Calcutta]].
He stood as the [[Liberal Unionist]] candidate for [[Clackmannanshire and Kinross-shire (UK Parliament constituency)|Clackmannanshire and Kinross-shire]] in the [[United Kingdom general election, 1892|1892 General Election]].
